body:
I'm in the process of learning game development and have a question regarding a simple rotation. So far, I'm visualizing the rotation as such: I've read this similar question but I'm struggling to understand how to apply this given formula: $$
\begin{bmatrix}
x' \\ y'
\end{bmatrix} =
\begin{bmatrix}
\cos{\theta} & -\sin{\theta} \\
\sin{\theta} & \cos{\theta}
\end{bmatrix}
\begin{bmatrix}
x \\ y
\end{bmatrix}
$$ Given a point of $(2,3)$, what would the point be after a rotation in the $xy$ plane about the origin through an angle of $-180$ degrees? $$
\begin{bmatrix}
x' \\ y'
\end{bmatrix} =
\begin{bmatrix}
\cos{-180} & -\sin{-180} \\
\sin{-180} & \cos{-180}
\end{bmatrix}
\begin{bmatrix}
2 \\ 3
\end{bmatrix}
$$ Is this correct?
